{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645099","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645099"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:12:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:12:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18085"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18085","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18085"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.96,0.04,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10799"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74164"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10799","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10799"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18085"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59655"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5741"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25153"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25565"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74164","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74164"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner for management of hypertension. She has researched her condition online but feels overwhelmed by conflicting information. During the consultation, she expresses uncertainty about treatment options and defers to her doctor\u0027s judgement, stating \u0022you know best.\u0022\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary source of power disparity in this clinical interaction?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cultural differences","Knowledge and expertise differential","Social class differences","Financial resources","Language barriers"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eknowledge and expertise differential\u003C/strong\u003E between healthcare providers and patients represents the fundamental power disparity in healthcare relationships. Healthcare providers possess specialised medical knowledge and clinical expertise that patients typically lack, creating an inherent imbalance in the therapeutic relationship. This is demonstrated in this case where the patient defers to the doctor\u0027s judgement despite attempting to self-educate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent important but secondary sources of power disparity:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECultural differences\u003C/strong\u003E may influence healthcare interactions but are not present in all clinical encounters and can be addressed through cultural safety training.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocial class differences\u003C/strong\u003E can affect healthcare relationships but are not an inherent feature of all clinical interactions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFinancial resources\u003C/strong\u003E may impact healthcare access but do not fundamentally characterise the provider-patient relationship in Australia\u0027s universal healthcare system.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELanguage barriers\u003C/strong\u003E affect only some healthcare interactions and can be effectively managed through professional interpretation services.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this fundamental knowledge disparity helps providers maintain awareness of their position of power and ensures they practice in ways that respect patient autonomy while fulfilling their duty of care.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Power disparities in healthcare occur when there is an imbalance in authority, knowledge, or control between healthcare providers and patients.","Healthcare providers have professional, social, and institutional power that can influence patient care decisions and outcomes.","Recognition of power disparities is essential for maintaining ethical practice and patient autonomy."],"references":["Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59655"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18085"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59655","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59655"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T22:52:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T22:53:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10799"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74164"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"